Hey Bimpe,

Yeah, I’ve been doing a short course on Python and texturing course as well. Just been trying to improve my portfolio. 

Also, I’ve just gotten a call from Simon Davies about me coming in for a Runner interview. I was wondering if you had any tips for me?

thats great! As cheesy as it sounds i'd say just be yourself! you're clearly passionate about what you do and what you want to do so keep that passion in the interview. Being a runner you'll be on your feet a lot and doing a lot of things like setting up meetings etc so its great to show you're positive , always ready to help and be a team player
